$interpreted: Tica: I need to breathe breathe breatheeee~~!!
Soohyeon: You okay, Tica? Just take deep breaths, you'll be fine.
Elio: Whew... I know we had oxygen herbs, but I still felt like I couldn't breathe...
Elio: Look how comfy Li-Hwa is down here. Perks of being a jellyfish, I guess.
Li-Hwa: It's a short distance. If it were longer, I'd need an oxygen herb, too.
Elio: That girl seems fine down here, too. You said she isn't a human... so what is she? Some kind of aquatic demihuman?
Li-Hwa: ...Let's get inside first, then we'll talk.
Tica: Ahh, so pretty! And it's dry! Are we really still underwater?
Li-Hwa: I'm friends with the maiden of this manor. She's even older than me. I'm watching the place for her while she's away.
Li-Hwa: But she's been gone so long, everyone thinks the place is abandoned. So it's not a bad spot to hide.
Elio: Hide what?
Soohyeon: Are you really going to tell them? If you do, then everyone here will...
Li-Hwa: I've been studying longer than other people's entire lifetimes. If I've learned anything, it's that there's more to the world than just qi energy.
Li-Hwa: Our world is a mystery. I don't understand it, and don't know if I ever will.
Li-Hwa: But I do know that I can't cure the bewitchers alone. I need them.
Soohyeon: I understand. If you trust them, then I trust them, too.
Tica: Man, I don't know what you guys are talking about at all.
Li-Hwa: Oh, sorry! Alright, everyone can come out now! We've got visitors.
Elio: ...Demihumans? Beasts? But...
Elio: No, you're not. And you're not humans, either...
Soohyeon: Bewitchers.
Soohyeon: For some reason, over the past few years, beasts have been mutating into something more akin to humans.
Soohyeon: We call them bewitchers. Most people in the east think they're, well... cursed.
Tica: So, you're a bewitcher, too?
Soohyeon: Forgive me for not properly introducing myself. My name is Kong Soohyeon of the Kyo Tribe. I'm the arbiter's daughter.
Elio: The Kyo Tribe? You're mythics of the Water Sect, aren't you?
Elio: Spirit water! You really are mythics!
Tica: Eh~? So she's a big deal, huh?
Soohyeon: No... Now I'm just a bewitcher. I'm cursed.
Elio: I don't get it... Regular people I can understand, but...
Elio: Someone as important as the arbiter's daughter? Wouldn't this be a bigger deal? Wouldn't so many from the Alliance be trying to help?
Elio: Why should you have to hide here at the bottom of the sea?
Soohyeon: Because, this curse... Even though I'm the arbiter's daughter, I still wouldn't be forgiven, or accepted.
Tica: What is that? Some eastern talisman?
Soohyeon: I think it's better that I just show you.
Tica: The plant mutated!
Elio: Be careful!
Tica: What was that!? It came out of nowhere!
Elio: What happened?
Li-Hwa: We call that being 'bewitched'.
Tica: Ohh, so back when you were talking about people being bewitched...
Elio: ...So they were touched by a bewitcher?
Soohyeon: Any living thing a bewitcher touches will turn. They'll turn into something just like that.
Soohyeon: And after you're bewitched, there's no fixing it. The only way out is death.
Soohyeon: ...That's why we're hated. Feared.
Tica: ...So it's the same as being bitten by a monster? You'll definitely die?
Elio: Seems so. So it doesn't matter if she's the arbiter's daughter, they'll want her exterminated just the same?
Soohyeon: That's right. And if it weren't for Li-Hwa helping us hide, we'd all be dead already.
Soohyeon: This talisman protects others from my curse. But, for some reason, I'm the only person it works with.
Soohyeon: And, like you've seen, there's a lot of bewitchers...
Elio: ...Is it really a curse? Or...
Li-Hwa: Listen, I'm a scholar. I don't believe in curses. But... no matter how hard I look, I can't find any other more realistic possibilities.
Li-Hwa: I just can't find the cause. At least, I can't do it alone...
Tica: Eh? You mean... you need our help?
Elio: So... the real reason you've called us here is to help you study these bewitchers? This curse? Nothing to do with runes or qi?
Li-Hwa: Yes, and no.
Li-Hwa: I do believe that the key to this curse lies somewhere in the relationship between runes and qi.
Li-Hwa: So I would like your help.
Elio: But, If we help you, won't we be seen as enemies of the Alliance?
Soohyeon: ...Yes, that is a risk.
Tica: And we might get locked up like Comrade Pang?
Soohyeon: ...Yes... That is also a possibility.
Tica: Wow~ Sounds like fun! As a Rune Academy elite, I feel like I can't say no!
Elio: You're right... If it were father, there's no way he would say no. We will help you.
Soohyeon: You...
Li-Hwa: Are you both sure? You don't need time to think?
Elio: This is about saving lives. That's what knowledge is for... this is my duty, as a student.
Tica: Don't worry about it, Miss Li-Hwa.
Tica: Headmaster Charle was our teacher, after all!

Soohyeon: ...Thank you... Tica, Elio... 
Thank you so much.
